{%- assign product = product -%}

{%- comment -%}
  Auto-detect a related bundle from /collections/bundles by tag overlap; fall
  back to the first OTHER bundle that is AVAILABLE. v18 (2026-05-26): both
  loops now require bundle.available so we never link customers to a Sold-Out
  bundle from the PDP aside.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign bundle_collection = collections.bundles -%}
{%- assign related_bundle = blank -%}
{%- if bundle_collection.products.size > 0 -%}
  {%- for bundle in bundle_collection.products -%}
    {%- if bundle.id != product.id and bundle.available -%}
      {%- for tag in product.tags -%}
        {%- if bundle.tags contains tag -%}
          {%- assign related_bundle = bundle -%}
          {%- break -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
      {%- if related_bundle != blank -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
  {%- if related_bundle == blank -%}
    {%- for bundle in bundle_collection.products -%}
      {%- if bundle.id != product.id and bundle.available -%}{%- assign related_bundle = bundle -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- comment -%}
  v18 (2026-05-26): the inline-FAQ-in-description workaround is gone. All
  product-specific FAQ content now lives in product.metafields.custom.faqs_v2.
  See also: how_it_works, why_we_picked, sizing_guide, who_its_for metafields.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  v18 (2026-05-26): single-dog rescue card removed. Replaced with three
  stacked left-rail cards rendered under the bundle aside:
    1. Tester card — all three dogs (Jack / Sophie / Molly) with photos
    2. Reviews snapshot — honest empty state pre-launch, Judge.me-driven once reviews land
    3. Ours vs General — brand-level comparison (no name-drops)
  Order chosen for scroll psychology: brand connection first (Tester), then
  social proof (Reviews), then rational comparison (Ours vs General).

  is_bundle is hoisted here so every downstream check uses the same flag
  (bundle aside suppression, "What's inside" vs "Why we picked it" card
  label, Promise card first bullet differentiation).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Bundle detection: primary path is bundle_contents metafield (data-driven).
  Tag fallback ('bundle' in product.tags) catches the edge case where a bundle
  is published before the bundle_contents metafield is wired up, so the Promise
  card and "What's inside" label still relabel correctly.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign is_bundle = false -%}
{%- if product.metafields.custom.bundle_contents != blank -%}
  {%- assign is_bundle = true -%}
{%- elsif product.tags contains 'bundle' -%}
  {%- assign is_bundle = true -%}
{%- endif -%}

<div class="product-page" data-testid="product-page">
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumbs">
      <a href="/">Home</a> <span>›</span>
      <a href="/collections/all">Shop</a> <span>›</span>
      <span aria-current="page">{{ product.title }}</span>
    </nav>

    {%- comment -%}
      v18 (2026-05-26): three direct grid children so mobile (1-col) order is:
        gallery → details (buy-box first) → side-cards (bundle + tester/reviews/compare).
      On desktop (≥768px) we use explicit row placement so .product-side-cards
      slots into the LEFT column under .product-gallery, while .product-details
      spans both rows on the RIGHT.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="product-grid-main">
      <div class="product-gallery">
        <div class="main-img" data-lightbox="{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 2000 }}">
          {%- if product.featured_image != blank -%}
            <img src="{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 1200 }}" alt="{{ product.title }}" data-product-main-img>
          {%- else -%}
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;height:100%;font-size:7rem;background:var(--color-mint);">🛍</div>
          {%- endif -%}
          {%- if product.compare_at_price > product.price -%}
            <span class="product-badge product-badge-sale">{{ product.compare_at_price | minus: product.price | times: 100.0 | divided_by: product.compare_at_price | round }}% OFF</span>
          {%- endif -%}
        </div>
        {%- if product.images.size > 1 -%}
          <div class="product-thumbs" role="group" aria-label="{{ product.title }} additional photos">{%- comment -%} v20 A6: was role="tablist" without tab child semantics, switched to role="group" so screen readers don't announce a malformed tablist. {%- endcomment -%}
            {%- for img in product.images -%}
              <button type="button" data-product-thumb data-img="{{ img | image_url: width: 1200 }}" data-img-large="{{ img | image_url: width: 2000 }}" class="{% if forloop.first %}is-active{% endif %}" aria-label="View image {{ forloop.index }} of {{ product.images.size }}">
                <img src="{{ img | image_url: width: 200 }}" alt="">
              </button>
            {%- endfor -%}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>{%- comment -%} /.product-gallery — closes here so side cards become a sibling grid child {%- endcomment -%}

      <div class="product-side-cards">

        {%- comment -%}
          BUNDLE upsell — left column under the gallery thumbs. v17 dropped the
          bundle hero image; "What's inside" thumbnail row pulls from
          custom.bundle_contents. v18 (2026-05-26): hide the aside on bundle
          PDPs themselves so we don't suggest another bundle when the user is
          already on a bundle page.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if related_bundle != blank and is_bundle == false -%}
          {%- assign bundle_savings = related_bundle.compare_at_price | minus: related_bundle.price -%}
          {%- assign bundle_contents = related_bundle.metafields.custom.bundle_contents.value -%}
          <aside class="product-bundle product-bundle-lowered">
            <div class="product-bundle-head">
              <span class="product-bundle-eyebrow">Bundle &amp; Save</span>
              <h3 class="product-bundle-heading">{{ related_bundle.title }}</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="product-bundle-description">{{ related_bundle.description | strip_html | truncatewords: 25 }}</p>

            {%- if bundle_contents.size > 0 -%}
              <div class="product-bundle-contents" aria-labelledby="bundle-contents-label-{{ related_bundle.id }}">
                <p class="product-bundle-contents-label" id="bundle-contents-label-{{ related_bundle.id }}">What's inside</p>
                <ul class="product-bundle-contents-grid" data-count="{{ bundle_contents.size }}">
                  {%- for item in bundle_contents -%}
                    <li>
                      {%- comment -%}
                        Each thumbnail links to its product PDP so a customer
                        previewing the bundle can dig into any specific item.
                        Self-link guard: when the user is ALREADY on this
                        product's PDP (item.handle == product.handle), render
                        a non-clickable span with aria-current so we don't
                        force a wasteful same-page reload.
                        Accessibility: the visible title span inside the
                        anchor forms the accessible name automatically — we
                        intentionally don't add aria-label.
                      {%- endcomment -%}
                      {%- if item.handle == product.handle -%}
                        <span class="product-bundle-contents-link is-current" aria-current="page" data-testid="bundle-content-link-{{ item.handle }}">
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-thumb">
                            {%- if item.featured_image -%}
                              <img src="{{ item.featured_image | image_url: width: 240 }}" alt="{{ item.title | escape }}" loading="lazy" width="120" height="120">
                            {%- else -%}
                              <span class="product-bundle-contents-fallback" aria-hidden="true">{{ item.title | slice: 0, 1 | upcase }}</span>
                            {%- endif -%}
                          </span>
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-title">{{ item.title }}</span>
                        </span>
                      {%- else -%}
                        <a href="{{ item.url }}" class="product-bundle-contents-link" data-testid="bundle-content-link-{{ item.handle }}">
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-thumb">
                            {%- if item.featured_image -%}
                              <img src="{{ item.featured_image | image_url: width: 240 }}" alt="{{ item.title | escape }}" loading="lazy" width="120" height="120">
                            {%- else -%}
                              <span class="product-bundle-contents-fallback" aria-hidden="true">{{ item.title | slice: 0, 1 | upcase }}</span>
                            {%- endif -%}
                          </span>
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-title">{{ item.title }}</span>
                        </a>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    </li>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </ul>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}

            <div class="product-bundle-cta">
              <div class="product-bundle-pricing">
                {%- if bundle_savings > 0 -%}
                  <span class="product-bundle-strike">{{ related_bundle.compare_at_price | money }}</span>
                {%- endif -%}
                <span class="product-bundle-price">Bundle: {{ related_bundle.price | money }}</span>
                {%- if bundle_savings > 0 -%}
                  <span class="product-bundle-save">Save {{ bundle_savings | money }}</span>
                {%- endif -%}
              </div>
              <a href="{{ related_bundle.url }}" class="btn btn-outline btn-block product-bundle-btn">Shop the Bundle →</a>
              <p class="product-bundle-note">
                {%- if bundle_savings > 0 -%}Saves {{ bundle_savings | money }} versus buying the pieces on their own. {% endif -%}Ships free on U.S. orders over $50.
              </p>
            </div>
          </aside>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          v19 (2026-05-27): bundle-own "What's inside" thumbnail grid. Mirrors the
          related-bundle aside above, but fires on bundle PDPs themselves (is_bundle
          == true) so a customer landing directly on a kit PDP gets the same visual
          breakdown of what they're getting. No "Shop the Bundle" CTA needed since
          they're already on the bundle. Items still link to their individual PDPs
          (self-link guard for the edge case where a bundle lists itself).
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if is_bundle and product.metafields.custom.bundle_contents != blank -%}
          {%- assign own_bundle_contents = product.metafields.custom.bundle_contents.value -%}
          {%- if own_bundle_contents.size > 0 -%}
            <aside class="product-bundle product-bundle-lowered product-bundle-own" aria-labelledby="own-bundle-label">
              <div class="product-bundle-head">
                <span class="product-bundle-eyebrow">In this kit</span>
                <h3 class="product-bundle-heading" id="own-bundle-label">What’s inside</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="product-bundle-contents product-bundle-contents-own">
                <ul class="product-bundle-contents-grid" data-count="{{ own_bundle_contents.size }}">
                  {%- for item in own_bundle_contents -%}
                    <li>
                      {%- if item.handle == product.handle -%}
                        <span class="product-bundle-contents-link is-current" aria-current="page" data-testid="own-bundle-content-{{ item.handle }}">
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-thumb">
                            {%- if item.featured_image -%}
                              <img src="{{ item.featured_image | image_url: width: 240 }}" alt="{{ item.title | escape }}" loading="lazy" width="120" height="120">
                            {%- else -%}
                              <span class="product-bundle-contents-fallback" aria-hidden="true">{{ item.title | slice: 0, 1 | upcase }}</span>
                            {%- endif -%}
                          </span>
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-title">{{ item.title }}</span>
                        </span>
                      {%- else -%}
                        <a href="{{ item.url }}" class="product-bundle-contents-link" data-testid="own-bundle-content-{{ item.handle }}">
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-thumb">
                            {%- if item.featured_image -%}
                              <img src="{{ item.featured_image | image_url: width: 240 }}" alt="{{ item.title | escape }}" loading="lazy" width="120" height="120">
                            {%- else -%}
                              <span class="product-bundle-contents-fallback" aria-hidden="true">{{ item.title | slice: 0, 1 | upcase }}</span>
                            {%- endif -%}
                          </span>
                          <span class="product-bundle-contents-title">{{ item.title }}</span>
                        </a>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    </li>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </aside>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          v18 (2026-05-26): three stacked left-rail cards replacing the
          single-dog rescue card. Order is intentional — brand connection,
          then social proof, then rational comparison. All three render on
          every PDP in the same order.
        {%- endcomment -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          1 — The Pack card. Eyebrow is "Picked with" (not "Tested by") so the
          card is true for both single products (we picked them with the pack
          in mind) and bundles (we curated the kit around what works for the
          pack). "Tested by" implied individual-SKU dog testing across the
          whole catalog, which isn't substantiated on most products.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <aside class="pdp-side-card pdp-tester" aria-labelledby="tester-title-{{ product.id }}">
          <p class="pdp-side-card-eyebrow">Picked by our team</p>
          <h3 class="pdp-side-card-heading" id="tester-title-{{ product.id }}">How we find things</h3>
          <ul class="pdp-tester-list" role="list">
            <li class="pdp-tester-row">
              <span class="pdp-tester-photo pdp-tester-photo-fallback" aria-hidden="true" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:1.8rem;">🔍</span>
              <div class="pdp-tester-body">
                <p class="pdp-tester-name">We research</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-role">Trends and real problems</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-line">We track what people are buying and talking about, then dig into what actually works.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="pdp-tester-row">
              <span class="pdp-tester-photo pdp-tester-photo-fallback" aria-hidden="true" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:font-size:1.8rem;">✓</span>
              <div class="pdp-tester-body">
                <p class="pdp-tester-name">We vet</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-role">Quality and honest reviews</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-line">Before anything lands here, we check materials, sourcing, and what real buyers are saying.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="pdp-tester-row">
              <span class="pdp-tester-photo pdp-tester-photo-fallback" aria-hidden="true" style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:font-size:1.8rem;">❤</span>
              <div class="pdp-tester-body">
                <p class="pdp-tester-name">We stand behind it</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-role">14-day returns, no runaround</p>
                <p class="pdp-tester-line">If something does not work for you, our return policy is clear and straightforward.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="pdp-tester-footnote">We only list things our team would buy themselves.</p>
        </aside>

        {%- comment -%}
          2 — Reviews snapshot. Honest empty state pre-launch (no fake stars
          or counts). When Judge.me writes data to product.metafields.judgeme
          (rating + review_count after first reviews land), upgrade the card
          to show real numbers automatically.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Rating is coerced to a number with `| times: 1` so a stray non-numeric
          value never leaks into the aria-label. The heading id is constant
          ("reviews-snap-title-...") and a heading element exists in BOTH
          branches so aria-labelledby never orphans.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign jdgm_rating = product.metafields.judgeme.rating | default: 0 | times: 1 -%}
        {%- assign jdgm_count = product.metafields.judgeme.review_count | default: 0 | plus: 0 -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Star rendering: build a filled/empty star string from the actual rating.
          Was hard-coded "★★★★★" — misrepresented sub-5 ratings.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign jdgm_full_stars = jdgm_rating | round -%}
        {%- if jdgm_full_stars > 5 -%}{%- assign jdgm_full_stars = 5 -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- if jdgm_full_stars < 0 -%}{%- assign jdgm_full_stars = 0 -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- assign jdgm_empty_stars = 5 | minus: jdgm_full_stars -%}
        {%- capture jdgm_stars_str -%}{% for i in (1..jdgm_full_stars) %}★{% endfor %}{% for i in (1..jdgm_empty_stars) %}☆{% endfor %}{%- endcapture -%}
        {%- comment -%} v19 (2026-05-26): hide the pdp-reviews-snap side card entirely when there are no reviews. The bottom "From the pack" widget already handles the empty state; duplicating "No reviews yet" twice on every PDP was a louder negative than a single empty state. Card returns automatically once the first review lands. Also softened "verified buyers" → "buyers" since Judge.me "verified" only means the buyer email matched the order — not that the review itself was vetted. {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if jdgm_count > 0 or jdgm_rating > 0 -%}
        <aside class="pdp-side-card pdp-reviews-snap" aria-labelledby="reviews-snap-title-{{ product.id }}">
          <p class="pdp-side-card-eyebrow">Customer reviews</p>
          <h3 class="pdp-side-card-heading" id="reviews-snap-title-{{ product.id }}">{{ jdgm_count }} {% if jdgm_count == 1 %}review{% else %}reviews{% endif %}</h3>
          <div class="pdp-reviews-snap-row">
            <div class="pdp-reviews-snap-rating">{{ jdgm_rating }}</div>
            <div>
              <div class="pdp-reviews-snap-stars" aria-label="{{ jdgm_rating }} out of 5 stars">{{ jdgm_stars_str }}</div>
              <div class="pdp-reviews-snap-meta">buyers</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="#ms-reviews-section" class="pdp-reviews-snap-cta">Read all reviews →</a>
        </aside>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          3 — Ours vs General. Brand-level differentiators that apply to
          every product. No competitor name-drops. If we later add per-product
          comparison data (e.g. custom.compare metafield), this falls back to
          that.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <aside class="pdp-side-card pdp-compare" aria-labelledby="compare-title-{{ product.id }}">
          <p class="pdp-side-card-eyebrow">The honest comparison</p>
          <h3 class="pdp-side-card-heading" id="compare-title-{{ product.id }}">Ours vs general</h3>
          <div class="pdp-compare-scroll">
          <table class="pdp-compare-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col"><span class="visually-hidden">Attribute</span></th>
                <th scope="col" class="pdp-compare-ours">Ours</th>
                <th scope="col" class="pdp-compare-general">General</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                {%- comment -%} v19 (2026-05-26): "Curation" → "Picked by" — owner forbids the "curated" word family as AI-tell. {%- endcomment -%}
                <th scope="row">Picked by</th>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-yes" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>Chosen by our team, not an algorithm</td>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-no" aria-hidden="true">!</span>Mass listing, no named tester</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">Returns</th>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-yes" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>14-day window, clear policy</td>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-no" aria-hidden="true">!</span>Varies by seller</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">Shipping</th>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-yes" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>Free U.S. over $50</td>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-no" aria-hidden="true">!</span>Varies</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">Support</th>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-yes" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>Real team behind the store</td>
                <td><span class="pdp-compare-icon pdp-compare-no" aria-hidden="true">!</span>Often automated only</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

      <div class="product-details">
        <div class="product-vendor">{{ product.vendor | default: 'SnagNest' }}</div>
        <h1 class="product-title">{{ product.title }}</h1>

        {%- comment -%}
          v18 (2026-05-26): Judge.me preview badge near the price is HIDDEN until
          the first real review lands. Pre-launch the empty "0 reviews" badge
          right at the buy-box hurts trust. The full review widget + the
          "Write a review" CTA stay visible at the bottom of the page (so
          customers can still seed reviews). When you have ~5 real reviews,
          delete the .jdgm-preview-badge hide CSS in this section's style block
          and the preview badge comes back automatically.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div style='clear:both'></div>
        <div id='judgeme_product_reviews_preview' class='jdgm-widget jdgm-preview-badge' data-id='{{ product.id }}'></div>

        <div class="product-price">
          {%- if product.compare_at_price > product.price -%}<span class="compare">{{ product.compare_at_price | money }}</span>{%- endif -%}
          {{ product.price | money }}
          {%- if product.compare_at_price > product.price -%}<span class="save-pill">Save {{ product.compare_at_price | minus: product.price | money }}</span>{%- endif -%}
        </div>

        <div class="product-trust">
          {%- comment -%}
            Trust pills. v18 a11y pass: every emoji wrapped in aria-hidden
            so screen readers don't say "truck" / "leftward-arrow" / "heart".
            HSPA spelled out (was "1% to HSPA" — opaque acronym).
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <div class="trust-pill"><span aria-hidden="true">🚚</span> Free over $50</div>
          <div class="trust-pill"><span aria-hidden="true">↩</span> 14-day returns</div>
          <div class="trust-pill"><span aria-hidden="true">❤</span> Team-picked finds</div>
        </div>

        {%- form 'product', product, id: 'ProductForm' -%}
          {%- unless product.has_only_default_variant -%}
            <script type="application/json" data-product-variants>
            [{%- for v in product.variants -%}{%- if forloop.first == false %},{% endif -%}{"id":{{ v.id }},"option1":{{ v.option1 | json }},"option2":{{ v.option2 | json }},"option3":{{ v.option3 | json }},"price":{{ v.price }},"available":{{ v.available }}}{%- endfor -%}]
            </script>
            {%- for option in product.options_with_values -%}
              {%- assign option_position = forloop.index -%}
              <div class="product-options">
                <div class="option-label">{{ option.name }}: <span class="option-selected" data-option-display="{{ option.name }}">{{ option.selected_value | default: option.values.first }}</span></div>
                <div class="option-values" role="radiogroup" aria-label="{{ option.name }}">
                  {%- for value in option.values -%}
                    <button type="button" class="option-value {% if forloop.first %}is-active{% endif %}" data-option-value data-option-position="{{ option_position }}" data-option-group="{{ option.name }}" data-value="{{ value | escape }}" role="radio" aria-checked="{% if forloop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}">{{ value }}</button>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </div>
              </div>
            {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endunless -%}

          <input type="hidden" name="id" value="{{ product.selected_or_first_available_variant.id }}" data-variant-id-input>

          <div class="product-quantity">
            <div class="qty-control">
              <button type="button" onclick="this.nextElementSibling.value=Math.max(1, parseInt(this.nextElementSibling.value)-1)" aria-label="Decrease quantity">−</button>
              <input type="number" name="quantity" value="1" min="1" aria-label="Quantity">
              <button type="button" onclick="this.previousElementSibling.value=parseInt(this.previousElementSibling.value)+1" aria-label="Increase quantity">+</button>
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" style="flex:1" data-product-atc-primary{%- unless product.available %} disabled aria-disabled="true"{% endunless -%}>
              {%- if product.available -%}Add to Cart · {{ product.price | money }}{%- else -%}Sold Out{%- endif -%}
            </button>
          </div>
        {%- endform -%}

        {%- comment -%} ============ v18 UNIFIED PDP SECTIONS ============
          Each section renders only when its metafield has content. Author copy in
          Shopify admin under Products → [product] → Metafields:
            • custom.how_it_works  (rich text)
            • custom.why_we_picked (multi-line, one bullet per line)
            • custom.sizing_guide  (multi-line, one row per line)
            • custom.faqs_v2       (Q|A~~Q|A multi-line)
            • custom.who_its_for   (rich text)
          The "SnagNest promise" is always rendered (shared template copy).
        {%- endcomment -%}

        {%- assign has_how    = product.metafields.custom.how_it_works -%}
        {%- assign has_why    = product.metafields.custom.why_we_picked -%}
        {%- assign has_sizing = product.metafields.custom.sizing_guide -%}
        {%- assign has_faqs   = product.metafields.custom.faqs_v2 -%}
        {%- assign has_who    = product.metafields.custom.who_its_for -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          Description handling: if ANY metafield is set, the description has already
          been migrated to structured sections. To avoid double-rendering the H2 blocks
          (which still live in product.description so the live v17 theme keeps working
          until v18 publishes), we render only the pre-first-<h2> portion of the
          description as a lede. Products with no metafields filled get the full
          description as before — no regression.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if has_how != blank or has_why != blank or has_sizing != blank or has_faqs != blank or has_who != blank -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            Description-lede extraction: when ANY metafield is set, render only
            the FIRST <p> as the lede. The rest of the description (subsequent
            paragraphs, <ul> bullets, H2 sections) is now sourced from
            metafields, so re-rendering it would duplicate copy.
            Safety: only do the strip when the description actually STARTS with
            a <p> tag (case-insensitive, whitespace-tolerant). If it starts with
            something else (an unmigrated future product with H2 first, etc.),
            skip the lede render to avoid producing malformed HTML like
            "<full description without </p></p>".
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- assign desc_trimmed = product.description | strip -%}
          {%- assign desc_head = desc_trimmed | slice: 0, 3 | downcase -%}
          {%- if desc_head == '<p>' or desc_head == '<p ' -%}
            {%- assign description_lede = product.description | split: '</p>' | first | append: '</p>' -%}
            {%- assign lede_text = description_lede | strip_html | strip -%}
            {%- if lede_text != blank -%}
              <div class="product-description rte">{{ description_lede }}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- else -%}
            {%- comment -%} Description doesn't start with <p> — extraction can't run safely. Render the full description as a fallback so we never ship a buy-box with no descriptive text above it. {%- endcomment -%}
            <div class="product-description rte">{{ product.description }}</div>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- else -%}
          <div class="product-description rte">{{ product.description }}</div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          Rich-text content check: rendering the metafield through metafield_tag
          gives us the actual HTML. We strip it to plain text and check
          non-blank — this protects against the case where a metafield object
          exists but its AST is empty (which would otherwise emit an empty
          wrapper div on the page).
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign how_html = product.metafields.custom.how_it_works | metafield_tag -%}
        {%- assign how_text = how_html | strip_html | strip -%}
        {%- if how_text == blank -%}{%- assign how_html = '' -%}{%- endif -%}
        {%- assign who_html = product.metafields.custom.who_its_for | metafield_tag -%}
        {%- assign who_text = who_html | strip_html | strip -%}
        {%- if who_text == blank -%}{%- assign who_html = '' -%}{%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          UNIFIED 4-CARD INFO STACK (v18 2026-05-26): every PDP renders
          exactly four cards in this grid — How it works, Why we picked it
          (or What's inside on bundles), the SnagNest promise (further
          down), and Who it's for. Sizing guide was previously a conditional
          5th card here; it moved to its own accordion below the buy-box
          so the grid count stays constant across all 36 products. Honors
          the owner's "ALL MATCH IN DESIGN" requirement without losing the
          sizing info for products that have it.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if how_html != '' or has_why != blank -%}
          <div class="product-info-stack product-info-stack-v2">
            {%- if how_html != '' -%}
              <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-title">✦ How it works</div>
                <div class="info-card-body rte">{{ how_html }}</div>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}

            {%- if has_why != blank -%}
              {%- comment -%}
                On single products, this card is editorial rationale ("Why we
                picked it"). On bundles, the same metafield holds a parts list
                ("Item Name: detail"), so relabel to "What's inside" and bold
                the item prefix — keeping the card chrome identical for design
                parity but the label honest about the content.
              {%- endcomment -%}
              <div class="info-card">
                {%- if is_bundle -%}
                  <div class="info-card-title">📦 What's inside</div>
                {%- else -%}
                  <div class="info-card-title">✓ Why we picked it</div>
                {%- endif -%}
                <ul class="info-card-bullets{% if is_bundle %} info-card-bullets-plain{% endif %}">
                  {%- assign why_lines = product.metafields.custom.why_we_picked | newline_to_br | split: '<br />' -%}
                  {%- for line in why_lines -%}
                    {%- assign trimmed = line | strip -%}
                    {%- if trimmed != blank -%}
                      {%- if is_bundle and trimmed contains ':' -%}
                        {%- assign parts = trimmed | split: ':' -%}
                        {%- assign label = parts[0] | strip -%}
                        {%- assign rest = trimmed | remove_first: parts[0] | remove_first: ':' | strip -%}
                        <li><strong>{{ label }}:</strong> {{ rest }}</li>
                      {%- else -%}
                        <li>{{ trimmed }}</li>
                      {%- endif -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </ul>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%} Specs / dimensions metafields kept for products that use them. {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if product.metafields.custom.specs != blank or product.metafields.custom.dimensions != blank -%}
          <div class="product-info-stack">
            <h2 class="product-info-stack-heading">Product details</h2>
            {%- if product.metafields.custom.specs != blank -%}
              <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-title">📋 Specs</div>
                <dl class="info-dl">
                  {%- assign spec_pairs = product.metafields.custom.specs | split: ',' -%}
                  {%- for pair in spec_pairs -%}
                    {%- assign kv = pair | split: '|' -%}
                    <dt>{{ kv[0] }}</dt><dd>{{ kv[1] }}</dd>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </dl>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
            {%- if product.metafields.custom.dimensions != blank -%}
              <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-title">📐 Dimensions</div>
                <table class="info-table"><tbody>
                  {%- assign dim_rows = product.metafields.custom.dimensions | split: ',' -%}
                  {%- for row in dim_rows -%}
                    {%- assign kv = row | split: '|' -%}
                    <tr><td>{{ kv[0] }}</td><td>{{ kv[1] }}</td></tr>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </tbody></table>
              </div>
            {%- endif -%}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          Accordions render in this order for ALL PDPs:
            1. Sizing guide (only if product has custom.sizing_guide populated)
            2. What pet parents love
            3. Shipping & returns
          The sizing accordion is FIRST so size-sensitive shoppers see it
          immediately without scrolling past general brand bullets. Open by
          default; What pet parents love + Shipping & returns are closed so
          one accordion sets visual focus instead of three competing.
          Pre-counts valid lines so we don't render an empty accordion shell.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign sizing_valid_count = 0 -%}
        {%- if has_sizing != blank -%}
          {%- assign sizing_lines = product.metafields.custom.sizing_guide | newline_to_br | split: '<br />' -%}
          {%- for line in sizing_lines -%}
            {%- assign trimmed = line | strip -%}
            {%- if trimmed != blank -%}{%- assign sizing_valid_count = sizing_valid_count | plus: 1 -%}{%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if sizing_valid_count > 0 -%}
          <details class="product-accordion" open>
            <summary>📐 Sizing guide</summary>
            <ul class="product-features-list">
              {%- for line in sizing_lines -%}
                {%- assign trimmed = line | strip -%}
                {%- if trimmed != blank -%}
                  {%- if trimmed contains ':' -%}
                    {%- assign parts = trimmed | split: ':' -%}
                    {%- assign label = parts[0] | strip -%}
                    {%- assign rest = trimmed | remove_first: parts[0] | remove_first: ':' | strip -%}
                    <li><strong>{{ label }}:</strong> {{ rest }}</li>
                  {%- else -%}
                    <li>{{ trimmed }}</li>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endfor -%}
            </ul>
          </details>
        {%- endif -%}

        <details class="product-accordion"{% unless sizing_valid_count > 0 %} open{% endunless %}>
          <summary>What our team loves about this</summary>
          <ul class="product-features-list">
            <li>✓ Picked by real people, not an algorithm</li>
            <li>✓ We only list things we would buy ourselves</li>
            <li>✓ Trending finds across home, kitchen, gadgets, and more</li>
            <li>✓ 14-day return window. See refund policy for terms</li>
            <li>✓ Ships in 1–3 business days from the USA</li>
          </ul>
        </details>

        <details class="product-accordion">
          <summary>Shipping & returns</summary>
          <p>Free U.S. shipping on orders over $50. Under $50, flat-rate shipping is calculated at checkout. We ship to all 50 states plus Alaska and Hawaii. Orders ship within 1–3 business days. Returns accepted within 14 days of delivery on unused items in original packaging. A 4% restocking fee may apply. <a href="/policies/shipping-policy">Shipping policy</a> · <a href="/policies/refund-policy">Refund policy</a>.</p>
        </details>

        {%- comment -%}
          FAQ rendering. ONLY renders when the product has its own FAQ content
          in custom.faqs_v2 (new v18) or custom.faqs (legacy v17). The previous
          generic shipping/returns/donation fallback duplicated content already
          in the "Shipping & returns" accordion + trust pills, so it's dropped.
          PDPs without product-specific FAQs simply don't show a FAQ section —
          shipping/returns info is still reachable above.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign faq_source = blank -%}
        {%- if has_faqs != blank -%}
          {%- assign faq_source = product.metafields.custom.faqs_v2 -%}
        {%- elsif product.metafields.custom.faqs != blank -%}
          {%- assign faq_source = product.metafields.custom.faqs -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          Pre-count valid FAQ pairs so we don't render an empty shell when
          all Q|A pairs are malformed/blank.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- assign faq_valid_count = 0 -%}
        {%- if faq_source != blank -%}
          {%- assign faq_pairs = faq_source | split: '~~' -%}
          {%- for pair in faq_pairs -%}
            {%- assign kv = pair | split: '|' -%}
            {%- assign q = kv[0] | strip -%}
            {%- assign a = kv[1] | strip -%}
            {%- if q != blank and a != blank -%}{%- assign faq_valid_count = faq_valid_count | plus: 1 -%}{%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if faq_valid_count > 0 -%}
          <aside class="product-faq">
            <div class="product-faq-head">
              <span class="product-faq-eyebrow">Good Questions</span>
              <h2 class="product-faq-heading">Frequently <em>asked</em></h2>
            </div>
            <div class="product-faq-list">
              {%- assign faq_opened = false -%}
              {%- for pair in faq_pairs -%}
                {%- assign kv = pair | split: '|' -%}
                {%- assign q = kv[0] | strip -%}
                {%- assign a = kv[1] | strip -%}
                {%- if q != blank and a != blank -%}
                  {%- assign open_attr = '' -%}
                  {%- if faq_opened == false -%}
                    {%- assign open_attr = 'open' -%}
                    {%- assign faq_opened = true -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                  <details class="product-faq-item" {{ open_attr }}>
                    <summary><span>{{ q }}</span><span class="product-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></summary>
                    <div class="product-faq-answer">{{ a | newline_to_br }}</div>
                  </details>
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endfor -%}
            </div>
          </aside>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          The SnagNest promise — shared across every PDP. Bundles get a
          slightly different first bullet because they're compositions of
          already-picked items, not separate picks (per the no-false-claims
          rule). Detection: a product with custom.bundle_contents set IS a
          bundle.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="product-info-stack">
          <div class="info-card info-card-promise">
            <div class="info-card-title">❤ The SnagNest promise</div>
            <ul class="info-card-bullets">
              {%- comment -%} v19 (2026-05-26): collapsed bundle/non-bundle branches into one line. {%- endcomment -%}
              <li>Chosen by our team, not an algorithm</li>
              <li>14-day returns. Up to 4% restocking fee, see refund policy</li>
              <li>Free U.S. shipping on orders over $50</li>
              <li>Trending finds across home, kitchen, gadgets, gifts, and more</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        {%- if who_html != '' -%}
          <div class="product-info-stack">
            <div class="info-card info-card-who">
              <div class="info-card-title">✦ Who it's for</div>
              <div class="info-card-body rte">{{ who_html }}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{%- comment -%}
  Mobile-only sticky ATC recovery bar (2026-05-24). Renders on every PDP but is
  hidden by default on desktop via CSS. On mobile it appears when the in-page
  primary ATC button scrolls out of view. Submits the same #ProductForm.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="product-sticky-atc" data-product-sticky-atc aria-hidden="true" inert>
  <div class="product-sticky-atc-inner">
    <div class="product-sticky-atc-info">
      <span class="product-sticky-atc-title">{{ product.title | truncate: 28 }}</span>
      <span class="product-sticky-atc-price">{{ product.price | money }}</span>
    </div>
    <button type="submit" form="ProductForm" class="btn btn-primary product-sticky-atc-btn" tabindex="-1" data-product-sticky-atc-btn{%- unless product.available %} disabled aria-disabled="true"{% endunless -%}>
      {%- if product.available -%}Add to Cart{%- else -%}Sold Out{%- endif -%}
    </button>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  /* Bundle aside lives in the left column under the gallery thumbs.
     Push it lower than the v13 default so the gallery + thumbs read first. */
  .product-bundle-lowered { margin-top: 4rem; }
  .product-bundle-lowered .product-bundle-cta { padding: 1.25rem; }

  .product-sticky-atc {
    position: fixed;
    left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border-top: 1.5px solid rgba(31,41,55,0.12);
    box-shadow: 0 -6px 20px rgba(31,41,55,0.08);
    padding: 0.65rem 1rem calc(0.65rem + env(safe-area-inset-bottom));
    z-index: 90;
    transform: translateY(100%);
    transition: transform .25s ease;
    display: none;
  }
  .product-sticky-atc.is-visible { transform: translateY(0); }
  .product-sticky-atc-inner {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .product-sticky-atc-info {
    flex: 1; min-width: 0;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .product-sticky-atc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .product-sticky-atc-price {
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: rgba(31,41,55,0.78);
  }
  .product-sticky-atc-btn {
    flex-shrink: 0; height: 44px; padding: 0 1.1rem; font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  /* Sticky ATC shows only at the single-column mobile width (<768px) so it
     never appears alongside the 2-column grid. v17 used max-width:1023px,
     which let it appear at tablet widths where the grid is already 2-column —
     violating the project rule that "sticky-bar breakpoint must be ≥ grid
     column-split breakpoint". v18 (2026-05-26) tightens to 767px. */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .product-sticky-atc { display: block; }
    /* Make room for the sticky bar so it doesn't cover bottom-of-page content.
       The padding applies to every section below the sticky-bar's z-index that
       extends to the page bottom — including the Judge.me reviews widget and
       the related-products grid that live outside .product-page. */
    .product-page,
    #ms-reviews-section,
    .product-page ~ .section { padding-bottom: 80px; }
  }

  /* ============ v18 PDP additions ============ */

  /* Unified section bullets — shared with .product-features-list style but tighter. */
  .info-card-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .info-card-bullets li {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.85);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .info-card-bullets li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 800;
  }
  .info-card-bullets-plain li::before { content: "•"; color: rgba(31,41,55,0.5); }
  .info-card-body { color: rgba(31,41,55,0.85); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .info-card-body p:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .info-card-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .info-card-promise { background: var(--color-mint, #e8f3ec); }
  .info-card-who { background: var(--color-cream); }

  /* ============ v18 grid layout override ============
     theme.css gives .product-grid-main a 2-col 1fr 1fr at ≥768px with default
     row flow. v18 has three grid children:
       1. .product-gallery (img + thumbs)
       2. .product-side-cards (bundle aside + 3 stacked cards)
       3. .product-details (buy-box + everything in right column)
     We want desktop = gallery top-left, side-cards bottom-left, details right
     (spans both rows). Mobile = stacked in DOM order: gallery → details →
     side-cards, so the buy-box appears immediately after the gallery — not
     after a wall of cards. */
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .product-grid-main {
      grid-template-rows: auto 1fr;
    }
    .product-grid-main > .product-gallery {
      grid-column: 1; grid-row: 1;
    }
    .product-grid-main > .product-side-cards {
      grid-column: 1; grid-row: 2;
    }
    .product-grid-main > .product-details {
      grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1 / span 2;
    }
  }
  /* Mobile order: rely on DOM (gallery → side-cards → details) but override
     to put .product-details BEFORE .product-side-cards using `order`. */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .product-grid-main { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
    .product-grid-main > .product-gallery { order: 1; }
    .product-grid-main > .product-details { order: 2; }
    .product-grid-main > .product-side-cards { order: 3; }
  }

  /* ============ v18 left-rail cards ============
     Three stacked cards under the bundle aside: Tester / Reviews snapshot /
     Ours vs General. All share the same shell styling. */
  .pdp-side-card {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-cream);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  .pdp-side-card-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-secondary);
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }
  .pdp-side-card-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .visually-hidden {
    position: absolute !important;
    width: 1px; height: 1px;
    overflow: hidden;
    clip: rect(0 0 0 0); clip-path: inset(50%);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* Tester card — three dogs stacked vertically */
  .pdp-tester { background: var(--color-mint, #F0DCC0); }
  .pdp-tester-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .pdp-tester-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .pdp-tester-photo {
    width: 64px;
    height: 64px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    object-fit: cover;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
  }
  .pdp-tester-photo-fallback {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1;
  }
  .pdp-tester-body { min-width: 0; flex: 1; }
  .pdp-tester-name {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .pdp-tester-role {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    margin: 0.05rem 0 0.3rem;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.78);
  }
  .pdp-tester-line {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.8);
  }
  .pdp-tester-footnote {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.78);
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Reviews snapshot card */
  .pdp-reviews-snap-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-rating {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-stars {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-meta {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.78);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-empty {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.78);
  }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-cta {
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.7rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(232,118,90,0.1);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }
  .pdp-reviews-snap-cta:hover, .pdp-reviews-snap-cta:focus-visible {
    background: rgba(232,118,90,0.2);
  }

  /* Ours vs General comparison */
  .pdp-compare-scroll { width: 100%; overflow-x: auto; -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch; }
  .pdp-compare-table { width: 100%; min-width: 280px; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  .pdp-compare-table th, .pdp-compare-table td {
    padding: 0.55rem 0.4rem;
    text-align: left;
    vertical-align: top;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(31,41,55,0.1);
  }
  .pdp-compare-table thead th {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.55);
  }
  .pdp-compare-table thead th.pdp-compare-ours { color: var(--color-primary); }
  .pdp-compare-table tbody th {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: rgba(31,41,55,0.85);
    width: 28%;
  }
  .pdp-compare-table tbody tr:last-child td,
  .pdp-compare-table tbody tr:last-child th { border-bottom: none; }
  .pdp-compare-icon {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 16px; height: 16px;
    line-height: 16px;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-right: 0.4rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .pdp-compare-yes { background: var(--color-mint, #F0DCC0); color: var(--color-text); }
  .pdp-compare-no { background: rgba(31,41,55,0.1); color: rgba(31,41,55,0.5); }

  /* Mobile: tighten padding on side cards, drop tester photo to 56px to keep rows compact. */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .pdp-side-card { padding: 1.25rem; }
    .pdp-tester-photo { width: 56px; height: 56px; }
    .pdp-tester-name { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .pdp-compare-table { font-size: 0.78rem; }
    .pdp-compare-table th, .pdp-compare-table td { padding: 0.5rem 0.3rem; }
  }

  /* v18 (2026-05-26): the desktop sticky-gallery experiment is gone.
     Everything in `.product-left-rail` (gallery + rescue card) flows
     normally and scrolls with the page. We tried two sticky configurations
     and both failed:
       1. Sticky gallery + sticky-bottom rescue card → the rescue card
          pinned to viewport bottom and overlapped the bundle CTA.
       2. Sticky gallery + static rescue card → at ≥1024px, scrolling past
          the gallery's natural position pinned it at top:1.25rem while the
          static rescue card below kept scrolling up, and the gallery's
          thumbnails ended up overlapping/covering the rescue card.
     The fundamental problem: a static sibling below a sticky element in
     the same scrolling container will always collide when the user scrolls
     far enough. Fixing this cleanly would mean (a) putting the rescue card
     INSIDE the sticky block (tall rail problem returns), or (b) moving the
     rescue card to the right column entirely (different design). For now
     no sticky — empty space below the rail on tall PDPs is the accepted
     trade-off. The mobile sticky ATC bar (<1024px) is unaffected. */

  /* Hide the empty Judge.me preview badge until the first review lands. The
     full review widget at the bottom of the page (#judgeme_product_reviews)
     stays visible so customers can still write reviews. Remove this rule once
     you have ~5 real reviews. */
  #judgeme_product_reviews_preview { display: none !important; }

  /* CRITICAL JM modal show fix (v18.2 2026-05-27):
     Judge.me's CSS sets .jdgm-write-review-modal__page + __section to
     `visibility: hidden; opacity: 0` with a 0.8s transition. JM only
     transitions them in via its own user-event-driven pipeline; when we
     call setup() programmatically the pages stay hidden (blank modal).
     SCOPED FIX: only force-show the FIRST page (review-form-intro) and
     the review-form-intro section. The other pages (review-details,
     about-you, share-media) stay hidden until JM's slider transitions
     to them, otherwise all 4 pages render simultaneously and overlap. */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__section--review-form-intro,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__page--review-form-intro {
    visibility: visible !important;
    opacity: 1 !important;
    transition: none !important;
    transform: none !important;
  }

  /* ===== JM modal brand polish (v18.2 2026-05-27) =====
     Override JM's stock CSS so the Write-a-Review modal feels like part
     of the SnagNest site, not a Judge.me default popup. */
  /* Container: rounded corners, soft shadow, brand fonts */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__content,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__container {
    border-radius: 20px !important;
    font-family: var(--font-body) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 14px 40px rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.18), 0 2px 6px rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.08) !important;
  }
  /* Title: Fraunces serif, dark text */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading) !important;
    font-weight: 800 !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em !important;
  }
  /* Intro / subtitle */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__intro,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body) !important;
    color: rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.78) !important;
  }
  /* Product title — Fraunces, semi-bold */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__product-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading) !important;
    font-weight: 700 !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
  }
  /* Close X: 44x44 tap target, hover circle */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__close-btn {
    width: 44px !important;
    height: 44px !important;
    display: flex !important;
    align-items: center !important;
    justify-content: center !important;
    border-radius: 50% !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    background: transparent !important;
    border: none !important;
    cursor: pointer !important;
    transition: background 0.15s ease !important;
  }
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__close-btn:hover,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__close-btn:focus-visible {
    background: var(--color-cream) !important;
    outline: none !important;
  }
  /* Star rating: brand orange. Stars are actually <a class="jdgm-star">
     elements inside .jdgm-write-review-modal__stars, not <button>s. */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-star,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-star.jdgm--on,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__stars a {
    color: var(--color-primary) !important;
    fill: var(--color-primary) !important;
    transition: transform 0.12s ease !important;
  }
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-star.jdgm--off {
    color: rgba(232, 118, 90, 0.28) !important;
    fill: rgba(232, 118, 90, 0.28) !important;
  }
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-star:hover,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-star:focus,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__stars a:hover {
    transform: scale(1.08) !important;
    color: var(--color-primary) !important;
    fill: var(--color-primary) !important;
  }
  /* Form inputs: site's contact-form style */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal input[type="text"],
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal input[type="email"],
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal textarea {
    font-family: var(--font-body) !important;
    font-size: 1rem !important;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem !important;
    border: 1px solid rgba(31, 41, 55, 0.18) !important;
    border-radius: 12px !important;
    background: #fff !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s !important;
  }
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal input:focus,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal textarea:focus {
    outline: none !important;
    border-color: var(--color-primary) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(232, 118, 90, 0.18) !important;
  }
  /* Labels */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal label {
    font-family: var(--font-body) !important;
    font-weight: 600 !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    font-size: 0.92rem !important;
  }
  /* Primary "Next" / Submit / Close buttons — match site .btn-primary.
     Actual JM class names: __nav-btn-next, __nav-btn-back, __nav-btn-close. */
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal button[type="submit"],
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__nav-btn-next,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__nav-btn-close {
    background: var(--color-primary) !important;
    color: var(--color-text) !important;
    font-family: var(--font-heading) !important;
    font-weight: 700 !important;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.8rem !important;
    border-radius: 999px !important;
    border: none !important;
    font-size: 0.95rem !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em !important;
    cursor: pointer !important;
    min-height: 44px !important;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease, box-shadow 0.15s ease !important;
  }
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal button[type="submit"]:hover,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__nav-btn-next:hover,
  html body .jdgm-write-review-modal .jdgm-write-review-modal__nav-btn-close:hover {
